1️⃣ Better Scheduling (Smarter Thread Management)

❌ Earlier (Java 21 initial behavior)

JVM used a basic scheduler

Not always optimal in:
-High load
-Mixed workloads (CPU + I/O)

✅ In Java 25 (Improved)

👉 JVM scheduler is smarter in:

✔ Work-stealing improvements
Threads are distributed across CPU cores better
Idle cores can “steal” work from busy ones

✔ Fairness
Prevents some threads from starving (waiting too long)

✔ CPU utilization
Keeps CPU busy without overload


🧠 Simple analogy:

Old → One worker overloaded, others idle
New → Work distributed evenly across workers

2️⃣ Less Overhead (More Lightweight Execution)

❌ Earlier

Virtual threads were already lightweight, BUT:
(i)  Context switching had some cost
(ii) Mount/unmount operations could be improved

✅ In Java 25

✔ Faster mount/unmount

When a virtual thread:
starts running → mounted
pauses → unmounted

👉 Now this process is faster

✔ Reduced memory footprint
(i)Stack grows/shrinks more efficiently
(ii)Better memory reuse

✔ Less GC pressure
Fewer temporary objects created

🧠 Result:

👉 More threads → less memory → better performance

3️⃣ Handles Blocking More Efficiently (🔥 Most Important)

This is the core reason Loom exists

❌ Problem (Traditional Threads)

Thread.sleep(1000);

👉 OS thread is blocked → wasted resource ❌

✅ Virtual Threads (Improved in Java 25)

✔ Smart Blocking Detection

When a virtual thread:

Calls DB / API / sleep

👉 JVM does:

(i)   Pauses the virtual thread
(ii)  Releases the OS thread
(iii) Runs another task

✔ Better Unmounting Logic
-Faster detection of blocking calls
-Less delay in freeing OS threads

✔ Improved handling of synchronized blocks

Earlier issue:

synchronized could block carrier thread ❌

Now:

JVM handles it more efficiently (reduced pinning)

🧠 Simple analogy:

Old:

Person waits in line holding a chair → nobody else can sit

New:

Person leaves chair while waiting → others can use it
🔷 Important Term: “Pinning” (Interview Gold 🔥)

👉 Pinning = when a virtual thread cannot release the OS thread

Happens in:
-synchronized blocks
-Native calls


Java 25 improvement:

-Reduced pinning scenarios
-Better detection + handling


